HEADWORD: Sendal
<hw>Sen"dal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>cendal</ets>
(cf. Pr. & Sp. <ets>cendal</ets>, It. <ets>zendale</ets>), LL.
<ets>cendallum</ets>, Gr. <?/<?/<?/ a fine Indian cloth.]</ety> <def>A
light thin stuff of silk.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>cendal</asp>,
and <asp>sendal</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wore she not a veil of twisted <qex>sendal</qex> embroidered with
silver?</q> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

